arChildNodes.szComment:
EXT. LAKESIDE - THE BLACK LAKE
Neyrelle’s magical motions QUICKEN. CLOSE IN: Her mother’s corpse begins to TWITCH.
Vhenard’s corpse JERKS and LURCHES upright, taking an unsteady step toward Neyrelle. She takes a huge gasping breath, refilling her empty lungs.
It looks DANGEROUS at first. Neyrelle shies away, ALARMED.
Vhenard is disoriented at first... her voice STRAINED with pain.
Neyrelle moves closer to her, trying to connect with all that remains of her mother.
Vhenard interrupts her by gently grasping her daughter’s hands.
Vhenard speaks insistently, trying to make Neyrelle understand.
Vhenard releases Neyrelle’s hands, a subtle reinforcement of letting go.

The Player takes a dagger and opens a small gash on their hand, dropping blood onto the ritual runes. 
Vhenard turns, cups her hands, thrusts her arms forward, and EXHALES.
A torrent of SMOKE-LIKE MIST spreads out before her, sinking into the BLOOD SYMBOLS she had been writing just before she was slain in the last encounter.
The blood symbols begin to GLOW. The water in the lake begins to RIPPLE - and a GHOSTLY BRIDGE forms on the water.
Vhenard reaches out a hand and loses the ability to stand. Neyrelle quickly moves toward her to catch her fall.
Neyrelle holds her mother for the last time.
